Write a program  in c to get a float value from the user and display it in the below-mentioned format. HINT: Use ceil() and floor() functions.

Input Format

Input consists of one float value.

Constraints

1<=n<10^7

Output Format

Output consists of one integer, its highest round off value and its lowest round off value.

Sample Input 0

54.5
Sample Output 0
54

#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {

 float n;
    
    // Taking input from the user
    scanf("%f", &n);
    
    // Calculating the integer part
    int integer_part = (int)n;
    
    // Calculating the ceiling value
    int ceiling_value = (int)ceil(n);
    
    // Calculating the floor value
    int floor_value = (int)floor(n);
    
    // Printing the results
    printf("%d\n", integer_part);
    printf("%d.0\n", ceiling_value);
    printf("%d.0\n", floor_value);




    /* Enter your code here. Read input from STDIN. Print output to STDOUT */    
    return 0;
}
